{"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/BuildingAMacOSVMManager","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"sections":[],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Compose the Spooktacular libraries into a first-class Mac app."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This article walks through the layered structure of the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Spooktacular SwiftUI app so you can build something comparable"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"without repeating the architectural decisions we already settled."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The app target depends on three Swift packages in this repo:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"code":"SpookCore","type":"codeVoice"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — pure Swift domain types. No AppKit, no"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"Virtualization","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", no networking. Use it for models, enums,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and protocol “ports” that describe what the app needs without"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"committing to a concrete transport."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"code":"SpookApplication","type":"codeVoice"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — use cases and services that combine"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"domain types into workflows (RBAC evaluation, tenant"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"isolation, runner-pool orchestration)."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"code":"SpookInfrastructureApple","type":"codeVoice"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — Apple-framework adapters."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Wraps "},{"code":"VZVirtualMachine","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"NSPasteboard","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"NSWorkspace","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"Security.framework","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"Network.framework","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"Foundation Models","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Views stay thin: they observe "},{"code":"@Observable","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" state objects and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"call through to these libraries. Keeping logic out of views is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"what makes the same codebase ship a CLI, a Kubernetes"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"controller, and an App Store binary from one package."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit"]]},"kind":"article","metadata":{"title":"Building a macOS VM Manager","role":"collectionGroup","modules":[{"name":"SpooktacularKit"}]},"seeAlsoSections":[{"anchor":"Related-Documentation","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/GettingStarted"],"title":"Related Documentation"}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/buildingamacosvmmanager"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"references":{"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit":{"title":"SpooktacularKit","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Create and manage macOS virtual machines on Apple Silicon."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit","role":"collection","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit"},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/GettingStarted":{"title":"Getting Started with Spooktacular","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"Create your first macOS virtual machine in minutes.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/GettingStarted","role":"collectionGroup","kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/gettingstarted"}}}